#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
dna_four_methods.py
===================

Single-file project containing the 4 final no-ECC image-to-DNA methods.

Presentation-friendly method names:

1. robust_low_resolution_image
   Display name: Robust Low-Resolution Image
   Stores only a small quantized image. Very robust, but blurry.

2. base_image_local_detail
   Display name: Base Image + Local Detail
   Main proposed method. Stores a robust base image and adds lightweight local detail.

3. base_image_webp_detail
   Display name: Base Image + WebP Detail
   Uses WebP-compressed detail tiles over a robust base image.

4. local_block_coding
   Display name: Local Block Coding
   Divides the image into small local blocks so damage remains local.

No ECC is used. CRC is detection-only, not correction.

Install:
    pip install numpy pillow scipy scikit-image matplotlib pandas

Colab:
    from dna_four_methods import run_benchmark, list_methods
    display(list_methods())
    df = run_benchmark('/content/blog_lofoten_islands.jpg', show=True)

CLI:
    python dna_four_methods.py --image blog_lofoten_islands.jpg --out results --methods all --show
"""

